DataElement.preferredName: Enneking Musculoskeletal Tumor Society Staging System Stage
DataElement.preferredDefinition: Text term used to describe the stage of the musculoskeletal sarcoma, using the Enneking staging system approved by the Musculoskeletal Tumor Society (MSTS).

DataElementConcept.preferredName: Enneking Staging System Musculoskeletal System Sarcoma
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: A staging system for malignant mesenchymal tumors that takes into account the surgical grade, local extent, and presence or absence of metastasis._The system of muscles, tendons, ligaments, bones, joints and associated tissues that move the body and maintain its form._A usually aggressive malignant neoplasm of the soft tissue or bone. It arises from muscle, fat, fibrous tissue, bone, cartilage, and blood vessels. Sarcomas occur in both children and adults. The prognosis depends largely on the degree of differentiation (grade) of the neoplasm. Representative subtypes are liposarcoma, leiomyosarcoma, osteosarcoma, and chondrosarcoma.

ValueDomain.preferredDefinition: A staging system for malignant mesenchymal tumors that takes into account the surgical grade, local extent, and presence or absence of metastasis._The extent of a cancer in the body. Staging is usually based on the size of the tumor, whether lymph nodes contain cancer, and whether the cancer has spread from the original site to other parts of the body.
